WEBVTT

00:02.580 --> 00:03.920
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:03.920 --> 00:05.620
I can't to lie you.
This is your baby.

00:05.620 --> 00:07.880
Sophie and Danny and Theo --
there's just --

00:07.880 --> 00:09.250
It's too much.

00:09.250 --> 00:11.210
They would never --
I know.

00:11.210 --> 00:12.670
The baby
has to be Jon's.

00:12.670 --> 00:14.380
Anybody at school
that you like?

00:14.380 --> 00:16.210
There is this one person.
Who is she?

00:16.210 --> 00:19.040
This new kid
at school -- Ella.

00:19.040 --> 00:20.620
You ever want to tell me
that Ella's a boy,

00:20.620 --> 00:21.920
I'm glad to hear that.

00:21.920 --> 00:23.460
I spent so much time
trying to figure out

00:23.460 --> 00:25.250
why you've done
the things you've done,

00:25.250 --> 00:26.880
and I realized
what I need to figure out

00:26.880 --> 00:29.290
is why don't I feel like
I deserve more.

00:29.290 --> 00:31.250
I can't be
your therapist

00:31.250 --> 00:32.330
and your friend
at the same time.

00:32.330 --> 00:33.330
That's not how it works.

00:33.330 --> 00:34.880
Okay, wait a minute.
Please.

00:34.880 --> 00:36.420
Do --
Do you have any idea

00:36.420 --> 00:37.750
what it took for me
to come here today?

00:37.750 --> 00:40.500
I-I don't have the courage to
talk to anyone else about it.

00:41.830 --> 00:44.040
Please.

00:44.040 --> 00:47.540
You wanted to enjoy
every moment of life, right?

00:47.540 --> 00:48.580
Here comes some life.

00:52.500 --> 00:53.380
[ Radio starts
playing loud music ]
Whoa!

00:53.380 --> 00:56.790
What is with that thing?
Oh, my God, Colin.

00:56.790 --> 00:59.380
Who still has
a clock radio anymore?

00:59.380 --> 01:01.540
I do. I've had it
since the seventh grade,

01:01.540 --> 01:03.540
thank you very much.
[ Sighs ] Well, Gary,

01:03.540 --> 01:06.620
you have a phone
with so many ringtones...

01:06.620 --> 01:09.250
Ah, yes.
...and beautiful, twinkly,
soothing sounds

01:09.250 --> 01:10.580
to wake up to.
Yes.

01:10.580 --> 01:12.880
♪ You can never know
what it's like ♪

01:12.880 --> 01:14.330
Please don't sing.
♪ Your blood
like antifreeze ♪

01:14.330 --> 01:16.750
♪ Cold as ice ♪
Your blood
like what?

01:16.750 --> 01:18.670
Antifreeze.
No, it's not.

01:18.670 --> 01:21.420
It's "blood, like winter,
freezes just like ice."

01:21.420 --> 01:22.920
What?
Excuse you.

01:22.920 --> 01:24.330
Blood is not a season.

01:24.330 --> 01:25.750
It is a liquid...
[ Laughing ] No.

01:25.750 --> 01:28.420
...kind of
like antifreeze.
Not antifreeze.

01:28.420 --> 01:31.540
Antifreeze doesn't even freeze.
It's in the name.

01:31.540 --> 01:33.750
♪ If you want to know
while I'm standing ♪

01:33.750 --> 01:36.170
♪ You just fade away ♪

01:36.170 --> 01:38.040
Here it comes.
♪ And don't you know that ♪

01:38.040 --> 01:40.960
♪ I'm still standing ♪
Remind me to never
go to karaoke with you.

01:40.960 --> 01:42.830
Remind me not to bring
a fact-checker to a
karaoke bar with you.

01:42.830 --> 01:43.920
No! No!
[ Grunts ]

01:43.920 --> 01:45.460
No, no!

01:45.460 --> 01:47.380
[ Indistinct talking
over radio ]

01:47.380 --> 01:49.540
Why would you do that
to Sir Elton?

01:49.540 --> 01:51.290
Oh, I love Sir Elton.

01:51.290 --> 01:52.880
It is this Rocket Man

01:52.880 --> 01:54.540
that is making me crazy.

01:54.540 --> 01:56.790
Colin, someone is
not a morning person.

01:56.790 --> 01:59.210
[ Colin whines ]
Susan:
...another one without
even a card from my father.

01:59.210 --> 02:00.710
Dr. Stacy:
That's on you, Susan.

02:00.710 --> 02:03.250
What you let happen
is what will happen.

02:03.250 --> 02:04.540
[ Radio turns off ]
[ Mocking ]
What you let happen

02:04.540 --> 02:06.040
is what will happen.

02:06.040 --> 02:08.250
[ Normal voice ] Ugh,
that woman is such a crock.

02:08.250 --> 02:10.790
All she does
is oversimplify everything

02:10.790 --> 02:13.290
and then hang up.

02:13.290 --> 02:15.460
[ Sighs ] Someone should
call her and tell her that.

02:15.460 --> 02:17.120
Maybe you should call her
and tell her that --

02:17.120 --> 02:19.000
that she's a disgrace
to your profession,

02:19.000 --> 02:20.460
that she's
a con artist.
Eh.

02:20.460 --> 02:23.170
She's like a depressing
fortune cookie.

02:23.170 --> 02:24.790
So call. Hey.

02:24.790 --> 02:26.120
What are you
waiting for?

02:26.120 --> 02:27.250
You don't have
a lot of time left.

02:27.250 --> 02:28.790
Gee, thanks!

02:28.790 --> 02:30.460
Hey, you're the one
who's refusing treatment.

02:30.460 --> 02:32.830
I'm just -- I'm employing
gallows humor.

02:32.830 --> 02:34.580
Yeah, I would call,

02:34.580 --> 02:37.210
but I don't think it would
be very dignified of me.

02:37.210 --> 02:40.170
Dignified? What do you care
about dignified?

02:40.170 --> 02:43.250
Call her
and tell her the truth.

02:43.250 --> 02:45.540
Make her blood run cold
like antifreeze.

02:45.540 --> 02:47.250
Oh, no.
[ Inhales sharply ]

02:47.250 --> 02:48.330
Hey.

02:50.290 --> 02:52.040
I dare you.

02:52.040 --> 02:54.120
Well, you know
I love a good dare.

02:54.120 --> 02:55.210
I know
what else you love!

02:55.210 --> 02:56.290
[ Laughs ]

02:56.290 --> 02:58.420
[ Screams ] Where are you going?
No!

02:58.420 --> 03:03.620
♪♪

03:03.620 --> 03:08.750
♪♪

03:08.750 --> 03:09.670
Regina: Rome?

03:09.670 --> 03:11.170
What is this?

03:11.170 --> 03:13.290
You are my life,

03:13.290 --> 03:15.290
and I will not lose you.

03:15.290 --> 03:17.120
[ Inhales sharply ]

03:18.420 --> 03:20.580
Baby?

03:20.580 --> 03:22.170
You -- You okay?

03:22.170 --> 03:23.750
Yeah. Yeah, yeah,
I'm fine.

03:23.750 --> 03:24.710
I'm fine.

03:24.710 --> 03:26.580
No, you're not fine.

03:26.580 --> 03:27.790
What's wrong?

03:27.790 --> 03:29.830
Just some stomach pain.

03:29.830 --> 03:31.830
I didn't want to say anything
after last night.

03:31.830 --> 03:33.540
Please don't
get worried, okay?

03:33.540 --> 03:36.500
Okay.

03:36.500 --> 03:38.330
Okay.

03:38.330 --> 03:39.830
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

03:39.830 --> 03:41.880
Who are you texting?

03:41.880 --> 03:44.210
I'm meeting a friend
at the arcade after school.

03:44.210 --> 03:47.000
Are you asking me
or telling me?

03:47.000 --> 03:49.290
Telling you.
I can't drive you
this afternoon.

03:49.290 --> 03:52.170
I'm sorry,
but I'm -- I'm busy.

03:52.170 --> 03:54.330
Don't worry.
I got it covered.

03:56.540 --> 03:58.830
"Don't know whether to call it
a date or not."

03:58.830 --> 04:01.830
Ah! Seventh grade
is so hard!

04:01.830 --> 04:04.120
Uh, "It's not a date.

04:04.120 --> 04:07.290
It's just hanging out
with your friend Elliot."

04:07.290 --> 04:08.620
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

04:12.000 --> 04:13.710
Gina? Hi!

04:13.710 --> 04:15.080
Regina: Hi.

04:15.080 --> 04:16.170
Hi. You okay?

04:16.170 --> 04:17.920
Yeah. Fine. Just --

04:17.920 --> 04:20.540
Rome has a stomach bug,

04:20.540 --> 04:22.580
so I think I should
stay here with him.

04:22.580 --> 04:24.960
I'm sorry. I-I don't
think I can go to your ul--

04:24.960 --> 04:26.790
Oh!

04:26.790 --> 04:29.120
Danny, sweetie, I finished
packing your lunch.

04:29.120 --> 04:31.790
Sorry.
Was I on speaker?

04:31.790 --> 04:34.330
You were. We're good.

04:34.330 --> 04:36.380
It's -- It's fine.
I can go by myself.

04:36.380 --> 04:38.170
I just --
I really didn't want

04:38.170 --> 04:40.000
you to go to your
ultrasound alone.

04:40.000 --> 04:41.880
Don't be upset.
It's --

04:41.880 --> 04:45.120
It's not my first time
at the rodeo.
No, I know,

04:45.120 --> 04:48.500
it's just it's your first time
without Jon, and...

04:48.500 --> 04:51.330
I'm just really worried
about Rome.

04:51.330 --> 04:53.000
I'm sure it's just
a stomach thing, right?

04:54.330 --> 04:56.540
Yeah.
Yeah, yeah.

04:56.540 --> 04:58.250
He'll --
Are you okay?

04:58.250 --> 04:59.670
Mm-hmm, he'll be fine.
Just c-call me

04:59.670 --> 05:01.170
when you're --
when you're done.

05:01.170 --> 05:02.500
[ Sniffles ]
Okay, yeah.

05:02.500 --> 05:04.620
Okay, great.
Great.

05:04.620 --> 05:06.620
[ Cellphone thuds ]
[ Sighs ]

05:11.830 --> 05:14.000
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Colin, what are we gonna do
about Danny?

05:14.000 --> 05:15.830
What's wrong
with Danny?

05:15.830 --> 05:17.420
He just needs a little help.
That's all.

05:17.420 --> 05:19.210
He doesn't want you to do
another one of those

05:19.210 --> 05:21.620
elaborate lemonade stands,
does he?

05:21.620 --> 05:24.380
The bamboo straws alone made it
impossible to turn a profit.

05:24.380 --> 05:27.040
I cannot picture you
at a lemonade stand.

05:27.040 --> 05:28.170
It's mortifying.

05:28.170 --> 05:29.420
I'm next. I'm next.

05:29.420 --> 05:30.750
You're next?
She's next.

05:30.750 --> 05:32.460
Don't follow me.
Stay here.

05:32.460 --> 05:33.960
No! I don't want you
making faces at me.

05:33.960 --> 05:35.830
Stop. Stop.
[ Laughs ]

05:35.830 --> 05:37.710
Where are you going?

05:37.710 --> 05:39.460
Cory texted me.

05:39.460 --> 05:40.920
He loved my set
last night.

05:40.920 --> 05:43.040
Like, "fist bump emojis"
loved.

05:43.040 --> 05:44.210
Of course he did
'cause you're the man.

05:44.210 --> 05:45.380
I am.
Who's the man?

05:45.380 --> 05:46.920
I'm the man, right?
That's right. Yeah.

05:46.920 --> 05:48.750
I'm gonna go to the club,
see if I can bump into him.

05:48.750 --> 05:50.000
Get him. Do it.
Maggie: I'm on!

05:50.000 --> 05:52.290
Whoa, what? This is it!
This could be epic.

05:52.290 --> 05:53.830
Do yourself a favor
and get to your car.

05:53.830 --> 05:55.120
Ha! It's show time.

05:55.120 --> 05:57.170
You, remember,
she's kidding.

05:57.170 --> 05:59.250
[ Beeping, volume increasing ]
Okay? Just
a fake question...

05:59.250 --> 06:01.120
to get her
on the show.

06:01.120 --> 06:03.250
Dr. Stacy:
Hello, Margaret.

06:03.250 --> 06:04.710
You're on
with Dr. Stacy.

06:04.710 --> 06:06.290
Margaret?
Maggie:
Yes, hi, Dr. Stacy.

06:06.290 --> 06:08.540
That's --
That's coming back.

06:08.540 --> 06:11.540
Um, so, I have
a bit of a dog issue.
[ Sighs ]

06:11.540 --> 06:15.040
It's not that I
don't like dogs. It's --

06:15.040 --> 06:16.670
It's just that
I don't like his dog.

06:16.670 --> 06:19.250
Like I said, kidding.
Um, he climbs

06:19.250 --> 06:22.120
in the bed with us.
Bleh.
You guys
have spooned.

06:22.120 --> 06:24.620
Maybe you're mad at
your boyfriend, Margaret.
Ooh, "boyfriend."

06:24.620 --> 06:25.670
Did you hear that?
And you're taking it out
on his dog.

06:25.670 --> 06:28.380
Because that's what it is.
That's what you call it.

06:28.380 --> 06:31.250
"Boyfriend," that's great.
Um, first of all,

06:31.250 --> 06:33.580
who said anything
about a boyfriend?

06:33.580 --> 06:35.460
How do you know
that we're not just

06:35.460 --> 06:38.250
"the word you can't say
on the radio" buddies?

06:38.250 --> 06:40.540
Are you asking him
to give up his dog for you?

06:40.540 --> 06:42.750
My God, that is so glib.

06:42.750 --> 06:45.080
You -- Okay,
you do not know anything

06:45.080 --> 06:48.830
about me or my friend
or his dog.

06:48.830 --> 06:51.540
What if I told you
that my friend is blind?

06:51.540 --> 06:52.830
Blind?

06:52.830 --> 06:54.080
Is he?

06:55.080 --> 06:56.750
No.
[ Snorts ]

06:56.750 --> 06:58.500
Okay.
Well, excuse me,

06:58.500 --> 07:00.420
but I don't think
this is why you called.

07:00.420 --> 07:02.250
Oh, great,
okay, excellent.

07:02.250 --> 07:05.040
Please, tell me,
why did I call?

07:05.040 --> 07:07.710
I'm saying this has nothing
to do with the dog!

07:07.710 --> 07:10.670
You're afraid to fully give
yourself to this relationship.

07:10.670 --> 07:13.290
Ooh.
That's your
professional opinion?

07:13.290 --> 07:16.460
You could fit that in
a fortune cookie,

07:16.460 --> 07:18.670
okay, lady? You know,
y-you're telling me

07:18.670 --> 07:20.040
that it's my fault that --

07:20.040 --> 07:22.830
that -- that I have
intimacy issues?

07:22.830 --> 07:24.880
That is -- Oh, my --
Do you know what you do?

07:24.880 --> 07:27.460
You jump to conclusions,

07:27.460 --> 07:31.170
and you shame people
in between toilet-paper ads.

07:31.170 --> 07:32.500
[ Knocking at door ]
What kind of --

07:32.500 --> 07:34.420
Wha--

07:34.420 --> 07:37.330
Uh, she cut you off at
"fortune cookie."

07:37.330 --> 07:39.250
Oh.

07:39.250 --> 07:41.080
That wasn't as fun
as I thought it would be.

07:41.080 --> 07:43.290
No?

07:43.290 --> 07:46.580
Maybe it's because she hit
a little too close to home?

07:46.580 --> 07:48.040
Hm?
[ Sighs ]

07:48.040 --> 07:50.920
Just saying.
I'm not talking
about this anymore,

07:50.920 --> 07:52.880
and, by the way,
you...

07:52.880 --> 07:53.670
[ Cellphone chimes ]

07:53.670 --> 07:54.960
...are it.

07:54.960 --> 07:56.620
I'm it?
Yeah.

07:56.620 --> 07:58.040
Oh, you didn't think
you could dare me

07:58.040 --> 07:59.920
and not get
dared back, did you?

08:01.250 --> 08:02.880
A dare game?

08:02.880 --> 08:04.040
-Yeah.
-Is that what this is?

08:04.040 --> 08:06.040
It is now.

08:06.040 --> 08:08.250
It's your turn
to seize the day.

08:08.250 --> 08:10.210
And, uh, how exactly
do I do that?

08:10.210 --> 08:11.460
[ Inhales sharply ]

08:11.460 --> 08:13.080
Oh, you are going

08:13.080 --> 08:15.040
to check
your text messages.

08:15.040 --> 08:16.460
And while you're at it,

08:16.460 --> 08:18.830
pick out a ringtone
for tomorrow morning.

08:18.830 --> 08:20.710
♪♪

08:20.710 --> 08:22.750
You're kidding me.

08:22.750 --> 08:24.710
And I want
a picture!

08:24.710 --> 08:28.620
[ Telephones ringing ]

08:28.620 --> 08:31.750
Carter, your standing desk
finally arrived.

08:31.750 --> 08:32.960
Well, you know
what they say --

08:32.960 --> 08:34.330
sitting is
the new smoking.

08:34.330 --> 08:35.830
Are we
loving it yet?

08:35.830 --> 08:37.540
It's a lot.

08:37.540 --> 08:39.250
I believe in you.
I wish you were my father.

08:42.830 --> 08:44.210
Well,
look what arrived.

08:44.210 --> 08:46.330
Hunter.
Looks great.

08:46.330 --> 08:48.000
Make me an offer.
[ Chuckles ]

08:49.790 --> 08:51.790
She busy?
Ah, she's swamped,
but go on in.

08:51.790 --> 08:53.170
Go on in.

08:54.920 --> 08:56.080
[ Knocks on door ]

08:56.080 --> 08:57.540
Hey, I don't
want to alarm you,

08:57.540 --> 08:59.830
but Carter said
sitting's the new smoking.

08:59.830 --> 09:02.880
[ Chuckles ] Carter's back
to his old desk by Wednesday.

09:02.880 --> 09:04.250
You want
the over or the under?

09:04.250 --> 09:06.420
Ooh, tough call.

09:06.420 --> 09:07.540
How long did he
keep the core ball?

09:07.540 --> 09:09.170
Four business days.

09:09.170 --> 09:10.210
But it took him two
to inflate it.

09:12.380 --> 09:13.710
Uh, hey, Henry called.

09:13.710 --> 09:15.830
He wants us both working
on the City Planner case.

09:15.830 --> 09:17.460
Well, he could put
four lawyers on it.

09:17.460 --> 09:19.710
It's a losing case.
Yeah, they were overbudget,

09:19.710 --> 09:21.210
there's clear negligence,

09:21.210 --> 09:23.040
and a paper trail
a mile long.

09:23.040 --> 09:24.670
Take a look
at my motion.

09:24.670 --> 09:26.620
I think we can get
the judge to throw it out.

09:26.620 --> 09:28.290
You're unbelievable.

09:28.290 --> 09:30.250
You know, when you win
this case,

09:30.250 --> 09:32.420
Henry's gonna
make you a partner.

09:32.420 --> 09:34.170
Might even buy you
a standing desk.

09:34.170 --> 09:36.380
[ Laughs ]

09:36.380 --> 09:38.710
[ Cellphone ringing
and vibrating ]

09:40.710 --> 09:42.040
Hey, it's Rome.

09:42.040 --> 09:44.330
I'm sorry to bother you,
but, uh,

09:44.330 --> 09:45.710
I'm in a lot of pain.

09:45.710 --> 09:47.420
What's going on?

09:47.420 --> 09:48.250
No, no,
not that kind of pain.

09:48.250 --> 09:50.710
Physical pain.
Physical pain.

09:50.710 --> 09:53.710
It's kind of all over,
but mostly in my stomach.

09:53.710 --> 09:56.120
You think the meds
might be causing it?

09:56.120 --> 09:58.710
Uh, th--that's
highly unlikely.

09:58.710 --> 10:00.120
Anti-depressants
aren't really linked

10:00.120 --> 10:01.500
to any kind of --
[ Groaning ]

10:01.500 --> 10:03.580
Oh...

10:03.580 --> 10:04.710
[ Objects clatter ]

10:04.710 --> 10:06.330
Oh! God!

10:06.330 --> 10:07.710
Rome. Rome?
[ Groaning, yelling ]

10:07.710 --> 10:09.790
Rome!
[ Stammers ]

10:09.790 --> 10:11.080
What's happening?
Hello?

10:11.080 --> 10:12.460
Rome, what -- what's
going on?

10:12.460 --> 10:14.290
Rome! Hello?

10:14.290 --> 10:16.500
Hello? H-Hello?

10:16.500 --> 10:18.290
Who's this?
Hello?

10:18.290 --> 10:20.210
Who is this?
Ma--

10:20.210 --> 10:21.420
Maggie?

10:21.420 --> 10:24.040
Hel-Hello?

10:24.040 --> 10:26.420
Yeah, Gina, Gina,
what's going on over there?

10:26.420 --> 10:28.380
I don't -- I don't know.
Something is wrong with Rome.

10:28.380 --> 10:30.380
I d-- I don't --
I don't know what to do.

10:30.380 --> 10:31.960
It's really bad.
Gina, listen to me.

10:31.960 --> 10:33.540
You need to take him
to Boston General.

10:33.540 --> 10:35.710
I'll meet you there,
all right?
Okay, okay.

10:35.710 --> 10:36.710
Baby, we got to go.

10:42.170 --> 10:43.620
Hey, kid.

10:43.620 --> 10:45.000
Yes.

10:45.000 --> 10:47.330
How about
some lemonade, huh?

10:47.330 --> 10:48.750
Forget about the sign.
It's -- It's free.

10:50.830 --> 10:52.170
Forget about
the lemonade.

10:52.170 --> 10:54.790
All I need is a picture
for my non-girlfriend.

10:54.790 --> 10:56.420
Here, will you just
take -- take one?

10:56.420 --> 10:58.380
Oh, come on.
What, that sounded weird?

10:58.380 --> 10:59.920
I'm s--
Come back.

10:59.920 --> 11:01.710
Kid, don't go.
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

11:01.710 --> 11:04.040
Oh, God.

11:04.040 --> 11:05.420
[ Scoffs ]

11:05.420 --> 11:06.790
Oh, hello, Margaret.

11:06.790 --> 11:09.170
Look, I don't have a good
picture yet, all right?

11:09.170 --> 11:10.380
A selfie's
not gonna capture

11:10.380 --> 11:12.250
the insanity
of what I'm dealing with here.

11:16.960 --> 11:18.460
Okay, I'll be
right there.

11:18.460 --> 11:22.120
♪♪

11:24.460 --> 11:25.830
Allergies?

11:25.830 --> 11:28.580
No. Yes.
Uh, Penicillin.

11:28.580 --> 11:30.290
Any recent
hospitalizations?

11:30.290 --> 11:31.250
No.

11:31.250 --> 11:33.040
Medications?
[ Sighs ]

11:35.250 --> 11:37.710
He's on
anti-depressants.

11:37.710 --> 11:40.080
Who prescribed them
again?

11:40.080 --> 11:41.880
Dr. Heller.

11:41.880 --> 11:43.380
Um, Sertraline.

11:43.380 --> 11:44.960
Two times a day.

11:47.000 --> 11:49.170
He tried
to take his own life.

11:49.170 --> 11:50.500
A while ago, I mean.

11:52.250 --> 11:54.250
Have you taken anything recently
that might have caused --

11:54.250 --> 11:57.080
No, no.

11:57.080 --> 11:59.500
Have you still been
having these feelings?

12:02.920 --> 12:05.710
Excuse me, ma'am,
could I speak to him alone?

12:05.710 --> 12:07.250
But he's my...

12:11.540 --> 12:13.120
Okay.

12:14.960 --> 12:16.380
[ Coins clinking ]

12:16.380 --> 12:18.290
[ Coins clattering ]

12:18.290 --> 12:25.500
♪♪

12:25.500 --> 12:26.790
Regina. Hey.

12:26.790 --> 12:28.290
Hi.
Hi.

12:28.290 --> 12:30.960
Where is he?
He's in --
in there, I think.

12:30.960 --> 12:33.330
They, uh,
asked me to leave.

12:33.330 --> 12:35.540
Hey, I'm sure they're --
they're taking good care of him,

12:35.540 --> 12:37.580
You know, that's standard.
They're just...

12:37.580 --> 12:39.960
trying to make sure that
the patient can speak openly.

12:39.960 --> 12:41.170
Rome tried
to kill himself.

12:43.170 --> 12:45.420
Is that...
why he's here?

12:45.420 --> 12:46.330
No, before.

12:47.620 --> 12:49.460
I see.

12:49.460 --> 12:52.420
[ Inhales sharply ]
I'm so sorry, Gina.

12:52.420 --> 12:54.500
Nurse: Excuse me, Mrs. Howard.
Yeah.

12:54.500 --> 12:56.830
The doctor would like
to order activated charcoal,

12:56.830 --> 12:58.250
and we're hoping --
I'm sorry.

12:58.250 --> 12:59.500
It can absorb
drugs in the gut.

12:59.500 --> 13:01.580
We typically don't pump
your stomach anymore.

13:01.580 --> 13:03.500
Oh, my God.
Do you think that
he took something?

13:03.500 --> 13:05.420
He insists he didn't,
but he's in a lot of pain,

13:05.420 --> 13:06.670
and his history suggests

13:06.670 --> 13:08.420
we should err on
the side of caution.

13:08.420 --> 13:09.920
He's refusing right now.

13:09.920 --> 13:11.380
You're his wife,

13:11.380 --> 13:13.210
and we'd like your permission
to be able to --

13:13.210 --> 13:15.120
What -- What -- What --
mine, why?

13:15.120 --> 13:16.330
It's Massachusetts
state law.

13:16.330 --> 13:18.210
If there's a suspicion
of overdose

13:18.210 --> 13:20.420
and he's a danger to himself...
Can you say with certainty

13:20.420 --> 13:22.460
he didn't ingest
anything dangerous?

13:22.460 --> 13:25.330
I-I don't know.

13:25.330 --> 13:27.080
I only found out last night
that he tried...

13:27.080 --> 13:29.250
[inhales sharply]
...to ki--

13:29.250 --> 13:30.460
Um... [ Sniffles ]

13:30.460 --> 13:32.080
He was in the bathroom
this morning.

13:32.080 --> 13:34.500
He doubled over in pain,
so...

13:34.500 --> 13:35.250
uh...

13:37.420 --> 13:38.960
Just do what
you have to do, okay?

13:40.620 --> 13:42.750
Please help him. Okay?
[ Sniffles ]

13:43.960 --> 13:46.120
It's okay.
Yeah.

13:46.120 --> 13:49.330
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

13:49.330 --> 13:50.790
Hello?
Cory: Eddie, hey, man.

13:50.790 --> 13:52.710
It's Cory.
Hey, Cory, yeah,

13:52.710 --> 13:54.420
I got
your fist bumps.

13:54.420 --> 13:56.080
Uh, sorry, I was gonna stop by,
but something came up.

13:56.080 --> 13:57.710
Oh, it's cool. It's cool.

13:57.710 --> 13:59.040
Hey, it was really nice
seeing you up there again.

13:59.040 --> 14:00.580
Yeah, it was great
being up there.

14:00.580 --> 14:03.040
Listen, that first song,
you write that?
Yeah, uh,

14:03.040 --> 14:05.380
writing was unexpected,

14:05.380 --> 14:08.000
so I called it
"Unexpected."

14:08.000 --> 14:10.210
I was just
thinking your song,

14:10.210 --> 14:11.790
it could be huge, man.

14:11.790 --> 14:13.330
I just
keep hearing, uh,

14:13.330 --> 14:15.120
KC's voice singing
that bridge.

14:18.250 --> 14:19.540
KC?

14:19.540 --> 14:22.040
Yeah, he wants
to record it.

14:22.040 --> 14:24.250
Wow. Uh...

14:24.250 --> 14:26.620
This could be big
for you, man.

14:26.620 --> 14:27.960
Yeah, but...

14:27.960 --> 14:29.540
Cory, this is my song.

14:29.540 --> 14:31.330
I wrote it.
Exactly.

14:31.330 --> 14:32.540
You could make a lot of money
selling songs.

14:32.540 --> 14:34.790
KC is on the verge.

14:34.790 --> 14:37.290
Okay, here's the deal.

14:37.290 --> 14:39.290
I don't know how, but...

14:39.290 --> 14:43.460
I got up on that stage
last night, and I had a blast.

14:43.460 --> 14:45.460
You can tell KC
he can write his own song.

14:45.460 --> 14:47.250
I got more important things
to worry about right now.

14:47.250 --> 14:50.080
♪♪

14:50.080 --> 14:51.540
My God,
this is disgusting.

14:51.540 --> 14:52.960
I can't drink
any more of this.

14:52.960 --> 14:55.000
I am telling you, it looks
and tastes like driveway.

14:55.000 --> 14:56.000
I'm sorry, dude.
You're drinking it.

14:56.000 --> 14:57.920
Let's go.
No, I'm begging you.

14:57.920 --> 14:59.040
Seriously, I'm literally
begging you.

14:59.040 --> 15:00.210
Just dump it
in the toilet.

15:00.210 --> 15:02.290
You're not
the boss of you anymore.

15:02.290 --> 15:04.250
Says who?
According to this chart,

15:04.250 --> 15:06.170
Regina.

15:06.170 --> 15:08.080
Hey.
Guys, what's going on?

15:08.080 --> 15:10.380
Tell me.
What is that?

15:10.380 --> 15:12.500
What is that? Is that charcoal?
Room-temp lava.

15:12.500 --> 15:14.500
I knew a guy --
sax player.

15:14.500 --> 15:16.500
Took so much molly once,
he --

15:16.500 --> 15:18.710
Whoa, no. Dude, did you
do something stupid?

15:18.710 --> 15:20.580
Dude, did he --
No, no, man, no.
This is ridiculous.

15:20.580 --> 15:21.830
I can't believe Gina's
making me do that.

15:21.830 --> 15:23.460
Really? I can.

15:23.460 --> 15:25.330
You tried
to kill yourself, dude.

15:25.330 --> 15:27.710
Maybe if you'd told her that
before she found your note,

15:27.710 --> 15:29.460
she'd be more inclined to
believe you when you say things

15:29.460 --> 15:31.620
and not in the waiting room,
scared out of her mind.

15:31.620 --> 15:33.670
So, bottom's up.

15:33.670 --> 15:36.250
Rome, I swear, I will pin you
down like I pin Colin down

15:36.250 --> 15:37.830
to give him
his doggy arthritis --

15:37.830 --> 15:38.880
[ Shrieking ]
Ooh...

15:38.880 --> 15:40.500
God.

15:40.500 --> 15:41.880
What is wrong
with him, anyway?

15:41.880 --> 15:43.500
[ Normal voice ] I don't know.
Just, like, some kind of,

15:43.500 --> 15:46.120
like, stomach pain, man.
Gary: It's a kidney stone, okay?

15:46.120 --> 15:47.580
I'm telling you.
I've had one myself.

15:47.580 --> 15:49.540
It's the worst pain I've had
in my life,

15:49.540 --> 15:51.670
but too bad.
Doctor's orders.

15:51.670 --> 15:53.620
Drink up.
I hate the both of you.

15:53.620 --> 15:55.080
Just do it.
I really do.

15:55.080 --> 15:57.120
I hate you both.
Imagine it's chocolate milk.

15:57.120 --> 15:58.580
You -- You pretend
it's chocolate milk.

15:58.580 --> 16:00.330
Here, take it.
You pretend you're
not a big, bald baby.

16:00.330 --> 16:02.710
How about that?
[ Sighs ]

16:02.710 --> 16:05.460
Who's our big boy?
Yeah.
Eddie: Attaboy.

16:05.460 --> 16:06.880
Okay, finished it.

16:06.880 --> 16:08.750
Ah!
See anything? Huh?

16:08.750 --> 16:10.500
You happy?
I'm happy.

16:10.500 --> 16:12.000
He's gonna be okay.

16:12.000 --> 16:13.540
Right?
Yeah.

16:17.380 --> 16:19.750
Regina, I've been
talking to him.

16:19.750 --> 16:23.330
Not as a therapist because
if I was his therapist,

16:23.330 --> 16:26.250
I couldn't be telling you this,
but as a friend.

16:26.250 --> 16:27.670
He came to me
after Jon's funeral,

16:27.670 --> 16:29.960
and I couldn't
turn him away.

16:29.960 --> 16:32.250
Wait.

16:32.250 --> 16:34.040
Talking to him
about what?

16:34.040 --> 16:35.250
About everything.

16:38.000 --> 16:39.420
Uh...

16:39.420 --> 16:41.830
I'm the one that referred him
to Dr. Heller.

16:41.830 --> 16:43.710
He's been trying so hard
to get better,

16:43.710 --> 16:46.210
and I have been holding my
breath waiting for you to know

16:46.210 --> 16:49.580
because as much as I hope
I've been helping him,

16:49.580 --> 16:52.080
I know that the person he
really needs to talk to is you.

16:53.920 --> 16:55.920
I'm so sorry, Gina.

16:55.920 --> 16:57.920
Look, I understand
if you're angry.

16:57.920 --> 17:00.620
The thing is, I don't have
time to be angry

17:00.620 --> 17:02.960
because I need to use
all of my energy

17:02.960 --> 17:05.460
to make sure that my husband
is gonna be okay.

17:05.460 --> 17:12.080
♪♪

17:16.540 --> 17:17.620
It's just an amazing...
[ Rome groaning ]

17:17.620 --> 17:19.330
...noodle place, dude.
I've been there twice.

17:19.330 --> 17:20.710
I've done takeout
so many times

17:20.710 --> 17:22.830
I know the delivery guy's
name is Mako.

17:22.830 --> 17:25.250
Why are you
telling me this?
I am trying
to distract you.

17:25.250 --> 17:27.750
It ain't working.
Well, that's on you.

17:27.750 --> 17:29.540
Oh, God.
Did Eddie go to find Gina?

17:29.540 --> 17:30.960
Yeah.

17:30.960 --> 17:32.500
I need to talk
to her, man.

17:32.500 --> 17:35.920
How could he tell Maggie
and not his own wife?

17:35.920 --> 17:37.960
What does that
say about us?

17:37.960 --> 17:40.080
Jon didn't
talk to me at all.

17:40.080 --> 17:42.620
You're asking
the wrong person.

17:45.290 --> 17:46.830
He drank it all.

17:46.830 --> 17:48.710
Seems okay.

17:48.710 --> 17:50.460
Said he wanted
to talk to you.

17:50.460 --> 17:52.620
Okay.

17:52.620 --> 17:54.080
You should go.

17:54.080 --> 17:55.170
What's more important
than this?

17:55.170 --> 17:56.710
Your ultrasound.

17:56.710 --> 17:58.040
Go.

17:58.040 --> 17:59.170
[ Quietly ]
Thanks, Eddie.

18:05.670 --> 18:07.540
She's right.

18:07.540 --> 18:09.040
These screenings are important.
You should go.

18:11.670 --> 18:12.750
I'll take you.

18:15.040 --> 18:16.290
[ Exhales sharply ]

18:16.290 --> 18:20.420
[ Inhaling sharply,
whimpers ]

18:20.420 --> 18:21.830
It's not just in my stomach,
you know?

18:21.830 --> 18:24.540
It's --
It's like all over.

18:24.540 --> 18:26.420
I'm telling you,
it is a kidney stone.

18:27.620 --> 18:29.830
Or you're pregnant
and the baby's breech.

18:29.830 --> 18:31.920
[ Strained laugh ]

18:31.920 --> 18:34.000
Don't make me laugh,
please.

18:34.000 --> 18:36.920
Ah!
[ Exhales heavily ]

18:36.920 --> 18:39.710
I was beginning to feel better
about everything, you know?

18:39.710 --> 18:41.620
Not great,

18:41.620 --> 18:43.460
but better.

18:43.460 --> 18:45.040
I promise you

18:45.040 --> 18:46.330
I didn't need
to drink that charcoal.

18:46.330 --> 18:48.460
I just did that
for Gina.
I know.

18:50.120 --> 18:52.460
I don't want to die.

18:52.460 --> 18:58.960
♪♪

18:58.960 --> 19:00.710
Okay, I'm gonna
leave you guys to it.

19:03.920 --> 19:05.080
You look uncomfortable.

19:08.540 --> 19:11.460
I wonder why.

19:11.460 --> 19:13.000
You should leave.

19:13.000 --> 19:14.540
I don't think
you should be here.

19:14.540 --> 19:15.880
This --

19:15.880 --> 19:17.670
This can't be our baby.

19:17.670 --> 19:19.500
Delilah,

19:19.500 --> 19:22.170
if you and I at least can't be
honest about this...

19:23.420 --> 19:26.290
...I think
that I will go crazy.

19:26.290 --> 19:27.580
[ Door opens ]

19:27.580 --> 19:29.120
Delilah. Hi.

19:29.120 --> 19:30.580
[ Door closes ]
I'm Dr. Mathers.

19:30.580 --> 19:32.500
Dr. Cohen was called out
for a delivery today,

19:32.500 --> 19:33.580
so I'll be seeing you.

19:33.580 --> 19:35.620
Okay.

19:41.920 --> 19:44.170
Number seven!
Pho!

19:44.170 --> 19:45.710
What I can't believe
is that

19:45.710 --> 19:48.670
we were keeping the same secret
about the same person

19:48.670 --> 19:50.500
while we were having sex
twice a day.

19:50.500 --> 19:52.380
I don't think
that Dr. Stacy

19:52.380 --> 19:53.670
would be
very happy with me.

19:53.670 --> 19:55.500
Oh, are you kidding,
Margaret?

19:57.170 --> 19:59.670
Talking to Rome --
far more professional

19:59.670 --> 20:01.750
than anything
that charlatan does all day.

20:01.750 --> 20:03.500
I mean...

20:03.500 --> 20:05.540
admitting that you're crazy
about your non-boyfriend,

20:05.540 --> 20:06.920
I could have told you
that one.

20:06.920 --> 20:08.830
The only thing I am crazy about

20:08.830 --> 20:10.580
is this ramen.
It's insane.

20:10.580 --> 20:12.080
Ah!
It's insane.

20:12.080 --> 20:13.920
God!
These are the best noodles
I've ever slurped

20:13.920 --> 20:14.960
in my fricking life.
[ Chuckles ]

20:14.960 --> 20:16.250
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

20:18.580 --> 20:19.750
Yes?

20:19.750 --> 20:21.250
[ Rome groaning ]

20:21.250 --> 20:23.420
You were right.
They just did an ultrasound.

20:23.420 --> 20:25.670
It is a kidney stone.
I knew it. I mean,

20:25.670 --> 20:28.170
I'm not board certified
or anything, but I knew it.

20:28.170 --> 20:29.540
[ Rome groaning, screaming ]

20:29.540 --> 20:31.330
Is that him?
Y-Yeah.

20:31.330 --> 20:33.460
He's just
trying to pee it out.

20:33.460 --> 20:36.080
Well, I'm with Maggie, and
I will tell her everything.

20:36.080 --> 20:37.040
Oh, she probably
already knows.

20:37.040 --> 20:39.540
Rome: Oh, God!
[ Groaning ]

20:39.540 --> 20:41.170
Tell her --
[stammering] it's okay.

20:41.170 --> 20:42.710
I'm -- I'm not mad at her.

20:42.710 --> 20:43.750
What?
What's going on?

20:43.750 --> 20:45.250
It's a stone.

20:45.250 --> 20:46.710
And she's not
mad at you.

20:46.710 --> 20:48.330
So, it's all good.

20:48.330 --> 20:50.120
Rome: [ Weakly ]
Babe. Babe, who is it?

20:50.120 --> 20:52.710
Your therapist.
Dr. Heller?

20:52.710 --> 20:54.960
Nope.
The one that's my friend.

20:54.960 --> 20:57.120
I know I handled it
in the worst way possible,

20:57.120 --> 20:58.790
but we were
just talking.

20:58.790 --> 21:00.120
Now they're just
talking to each other.

21:00.120 --> 21:03.000
It's not that
you were talking to her.

21:03.000 --> 21:04.620
It's that you
weren't talking to me.

21:04.620 --> 21:07.670
I know, but...

21:07.670 --> 21:08.830
Gina, if I'd have
told it to you,

21:08.830 --> 21:10.620
it would have made it
too real.

21:10.620 --> 21:12.880
[ Whimpering ]

21:12.880 --> 21:14.880
[ Screaming ] Oh, God!

21:14.880 --> 21:16.080
Oh, my.
Yeah.

21:16.080 --> 21:18.750
Oh, God!

21:18.750 --> 21:20.540
Well, it sounds like he's making
some real progress over there.

21:20.540 --> 21:22.040
Regina: Yeah.
His best day ever.

21:22.040 --> 21:23.750
Ooh-hoo-hoo!

21:24.710 --> 21:26.080
Rome?

21:27.500 --> 21:28.830
Rome?

21:28.830 --> 21:31.500
I think he just passed it.
I have to go.

21:31.500 --> 21:33.170
Do you need me
to come in?

21:33.170 --> 21:35.120
Hey.

21:35.120 --> 21:36.250
[ Sighing ]
It came out.

21:36.250 --> 21:37.500
You want to see it?
It's so small.

21:37.500 --> 21:39.540
How could something so small
cause so much pain?

21:39.540 --> 21:41.580
Don't flush it.
They want you to save it.

21:41.580 --> 21:43.750
Are you crazy? That thing's
going straight to the harbor.

21:43.750 --> 21:45.620
I don't want to see
that thing again.

21:45.620 --> 21:50.500
♪♪

21:50.500 --> 21:52.460
I am so sorry, babe.

21:52.460 --> 21:57.170
♪♪

21:57.170 --> 21:59.000
I am sorry
for everything, Gina.

22:00.330 --> 22:01.920
I know.

22:05.210 --> 22:06.330
They're gonna be okay.

22:08.040 --> 22:09.920
It's gonna take
a little time.

22:09.920 --> 22:11.380
Mm-hmm.

22:11.380 --> 22:12.580
You're it,
by the way.

22:12.580 --> 22:13.790
What? No.

22:13.790 --> 22:15.210
I didn't see a pic.

22:16.420 --> 22:17.620
No, no, no.
No pics.

22:17.620 --> 22:19.210
Look, I did it.

22:19.210 --> 22:21.290
You know I did it.
It was weird.

22:21.290 --> 22:23.080
No! A picture --
that was the deal.

22:23.080 --> 22:25.540
And if there is anything
that you and I know about,

22:25.540 --> 22:27.330
it's a deal.

22:27.330 --> 22:29.540
I'm not doing
another lemonade stand.

22:29.540 --> 22:30.830
Cashier: Number 7!

22:30.830 --> 22:32.330
You called
into the radio,

22:32.330 --> 22:33.880
I scared a small child.
We're square.

22:33.880 --> 22:35.580
[ Laughs ]
Number 24!

22:35.580 --> 22:37.170
Ugh, enough with
the microphone.

22:37.170 --> 22:38.830
Number 24!

22:38.830 --> 22:40.000
I have a good idea.

22:41.420 --> 22:44.210
I dare you
to go steal her mic

22:44.210 --> 22:46.750
and sing
"I'm Still Standing."

22:46.750 --> 22:48.120
Your version,

22:48.120 --> 22:49.920
wrong lyrics and all.

22:49.920 --> 22:52.380
Go on, Rocket Man.
What are you waiting for?

22:52.380 --> 22:54.710
Hey, I don't have that
much time left, remember?

22:54.710 --> 22:56.000
Number 27!

22:56.000 --> 22:58.120
What are you
so afraid of?

22:58.120 --> 22:59.710
Perhaps
you've forgotten...

22:59.710 --> 23:01.920
I'm only scared of heights
and public bathrooms.

23:01.920 --> 23:04.460
[ Laughs ]

23:04.460 --> 23:06.000
Oh, get up,
'cause you're coming with me.

23:06.000 --> 23:07.080
No, I'm not.
Oh, no,

23:07.080 --> 23:08.210
this is a duet

23:08.210 --> 23:10.790
because I dare you
to sing backup.

23:10.790 --> 23:13.580
Come on.
That's right.
We're in this together.

23:13.580 --> 23:15.380
Uh, pardon me.

23:15.380 --> 23:18.330
I, uh -- I ordered
the microphone.
Excuse me?

23:18.330 --> 23:19.830
Don't you know the customer
is always right?

23:19.830 --> 23:24.170
Hello, patrons
of Win's Dumpling Palace.

23:24.170 --> 23:25.380
This one here goes out

23:25.380 --> 23:27.290
to everybody who wants
to be loved,

23:27.290 --> 23:29.620
even if
you don't know how.

23:29.620 --> 23:30.920
[ Fingers snapping ]

23:33.000 --> 23:35.620
♪ You could never
know what it's like ♪

23:35.620 --> 23:37.920
♪ You're cold like antifreeze,
just like ice ♪

23:37.920 --> 23:40.500
♪ You got a cold, lonely light
that shines from you ♪

23:40.500 --> 23:42.040
♪ You'll wind up
like the wreck ♪

23:42.040 --> 23:45.000
♪ You hide behind
that mask you use ♪

23:47.380 --> 23:49.540
♪ And did you think this fool
could never win ♪

23:49.540 --> 23:52.120
♪ Well, look at me,
I'm coming back again ♪

23:52.120 --> 23:54.670
♪ I got a taste of love
in a simple way ♪

23:54.670 --> 23:57.120
♪ And if you need to know
while I'm still standing ♪

23:57.120 --> 23:59.330
♪ You just fade away ♪

23:59.330 --> 24:00.620
♪ Don't you know ♪

24:00.620 --> 24:02.710
Both:
♪ I'm still standing ♪

24:02.710 --> 24:05.170
♪ Better than I ever did ♪

24:05.170 --> 24:07.790
♪ Looking like a true survivor ♪

24:07.790 --> 24:11.120
♪ Feeling
like a little kid ♪

24:11.120 --> 24:13.000
♪ I'm still standing ♪

24:13.000 --> 24:15.670
♪ After all this time ♪

24:15.670 --> 24:18.210
♪ Picking up
the pieces of my life ♪

24:18.210 --> 24:20.540
♪ Without you on my mind ♪

24:20.540 --> 24:23.120
I can't believe that
little guy is in there.

24:23.120 --> 24:24.960
Hm, or girl.

24:24.960 --> 24:26.040
Do you want
to know?

24:26.040 --> 24:28.170
No.
[ Chuckles ]

24:28.170 --> 24:31.170
It's too early
to say anyway.

24:31.170 --> 24:33.380
That's your baby.
[ Chuckles ]

24:33.380 --> 24:35.290
[ Quietly ]
Oh, my God...

24:35.290 --> 24:37.710
Oh, my God.
[ Exhales sharply ]

24:37.710 --> 24:39.000
[ Gasps ]
It's moving.

24:39.000 --> 24:41.460
[ Chuckles ]
That's the idea.

24:41.460 --> 24:44.620
Look at you go.
[ Chuckles ]

24:44.620 --> 24:46.420
Gary and Maggie:
♪ I'm still standing ♪

24:46.420 --> 24:49.210
♪ Better than I ever did ♪

24:49.210 --> 24:51.920
♪ Looking like a true survivor ♪

24:51.920 --> 24:55.120
♪ Feeling like a little kid ♪

24:55.120 --> 24:57.290
♪ I'm still standing ♪

24:57.290 --> 25:00.080
♪ After all this time ♪

25:00.080 --> 25:02.170
♪ Picking up
the pieces of my life ♪

25:02.170 --> 25:04.920
♪ Without you on my mind ♪

25:04.920 --> 25:07.420
♪ I'm still standing ♪

25:07.420 --> 25:10.290
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

25:10.290 --> 25:12.920
♪ I'm still standing ♪

25:12.920 --> 25:15.960
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

25:15.960 --> 25:18.120
♪ I'm still standing ♪

25:18.120 --> 25:21.250
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

25:21.250 --> 25:23.710
♪ I'm still standing ♪

25:23.710 --> 25:25.460
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

25:25.460 --> 25:34.080
♪♪

25:34.080 --> 25:42.920
♪♪

25:42.920 --> 25:45.250
Dr. Mathers:
That little flutter
is the heartbeat.

25:45.250 --> 25:48.040
It looks like a butterfly.
[ Chuckles ]

25:48.040 --> 25:50.670
Would you like
to hear it?

25:50.670 --> 25:53.250
The heartbeat?

25:53.250 --> 25:54.880
Can we?

25:54.880 --> 25:56.250
We can arrange that.

25:58.040 --> 25:59.670
[ Heart beating steadily ]

26:03.540 --> 26:06.290
[ Sighs ]

26:06.290 --> 26:08.670
Heartbeat's
perfectly normal.

26:08.670 --> 26:11.960
♪♪

26:11.960 --> 26:13.170
I'm sorry.

26:15.750 --> 26:17.210
I need a minute.

26:17.210 --> 26:19.920
[ Door opens, closes ]

26:19.920 --> 26:21.420
Dads are
always emotional.

26:21.420 --> 26:23.710
[ Sighs, sniffles ]

26:29.670 --> 26:30.670
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

26:30.670 --> 26:32.250
That's a winner.
Yeah.

26:32.250 --> 26:33.790
Thank you. [ Chuckles ]
Take care, guys.

26:33.790 --> 26:35.040
All right, well,

26:35.040 --> 26:37.000
technically,
now you're it.

26:37.000 --> 26:39.040
Stop. Can we just enjoy
our 15 minutes, please?

26:39.040 --> 26:40.960
All right, we were fierce.
I'll give you that.

26:41.960 --> 26:43.210
[ Chuckles ]

26:43.210 --> 26:45.040
Whoa, what is that?

26:45.040 --> 26:47.670
Oh, it's a bruise.
Did I do that?

26:47.670 --> 26:49.620
I know I can get
a little rowdy --
Oh, no, no, no.

26:49.620 --> 26:51.250
It was just -- uh --
It's been there for a few days.

26:53.170 --> 26:55.580
I'm gonna
bruise more easily.

26:55.580 --> 26:57.420
It's, you know, -- The disease
messes with your blood.

26:57.420 --> 27:00.000
I know what it does.

27:00.000 --> 27:01.790
This is really happening,
isn't it?
Hey,

27:01.790 --> 27:03.540
Gary, I feel fine.

27:03.540 --> 27:05.750
Okay.
Come on. Don't go soft on me.

27:05.750 --> 27:06.830
We have a deal.

27:08.710 --> 27:10.080
You know, I dare you
to show the world --

27:10.080 --> 27:11.330
I don't feel like it.

27:11.330 --> 27:14.250
I dare you

27:14.250 --> 27:17.380
to show the world
that you are not afraid...

27:17.380 --> 27:18.330
of anything.

27:20.750 --> 27:22.210
How do I do that?

27:22.210 --> 27:25.170
[ Sighs ]
I don't know.

27:25.170 --> 27:26.620
You're gonna
have to figure that out.

27:31.710 --> 27:33.460
Eddie: Cute kid.

27:33.460 --> 27:35.880
Could definitely use
some arms and legs,

27:35.880 --> 27:38.500
but give him some time.

27:38.500 --> 27:39.710
I'm so sorry, Eddie.

27:39.710 --> 27:40.790
May-Maybe --
Don't be.

27:42.710 --> 27:45.380
This is amazing.

27:45.380 --> 27:47.670
And I just want
what's best for you.

27:47.670 --> 27:49.040
Pretending
you're not the father,

27:49.040 --> 27:50.710
I know
it's unbearable.

27:50.710 --> 27:53.420
It's got to be the hardest thing
I've ever done in my life.

27:56.330 --> 27:59.290
But sometimes
you don't get to do...

27:59.290 --> 28:01.830
the fun thing, the thing
that makes you happy.

28:03.960 --> 28:05.080
You have to do
the right thing.

28:09.540 --> 28:12.250
I'm gonna say this,

28:12.250 --> 28:13.750
and I'll never
say it again.

28:15.830 --> 28:19.380
Whatever we did,
whatever happened...

28:22.210 --> 28:24.210
...we also created a life.

28:32.290 --> 28:34.170
-I want to snuggle --
-[ Laughing ] I want to marry --

28:34.170 --> 28:36.080
KC:
Look at -- [ Laughs ]

28:36.080 --> 28:39.000
Hey.

28:39.000 --> 28:40.080
Eddie!

28:42.420 --> 28:44.290
You want a beer?

28:44.290 --> 28:45.880
Oh, that's right.

28:45.880 --> 28:48.500
You don't drink.
He doesn't drink.

28:48.500 --> 28:49.830
So, you gonna sell me
that song or what, man?

28:49.830 --> 28:51.960
'Cause it's
a pretty good song.

28:51.960 --> 28:54.170
Yeah, I am.
You are?

28:54.170 --> 28:55.880
You're lucky.

28:55.880 --> 28:58.170
You caught me
on the exact right day.

28:58.170 --> 28:59.580
Great, 'cause I want
to screw with it

28:59.580 --> 29:00.710
just a little bit.
I mean,

29:00.710 --> 29:02.330
I think the bridge
definitely needs

29:02.330 --> 29:04.420
a little somethin'
somethin', right?

29:04.420 --> 29:07.540
Yeah. Do whatever you want.
My man.

29:07.540 --> 29:09.750
Yeah.
Hey, thank you.
Seriously, bro.

29:09.750 --> 29:11.210
Yeah.
Thank you.

29:11.210 --> 29:12.040
Hey.

29:12.040 --> 29:14.080
Yeah, listen...

29:14.080 --> 29:16.000
You know what? You might
make it big one day.

29:17.580 --> 29:20.960
But I suggest you
put down that bottle.

29:20.960 --> 29:23.960
Because you don't want
to end up like me --

29:23.960 --> 29:27.830
forced to sell
a great song to...

29:27.830 --> 29:29.040
someone like you.

29:30.880 --> 29:32.120
[ Pats arm ]

29:37.880 --> 29:39.170
[ Quietly ]
Thanks, man.

29:39.170 --> 29:42.170
All signed out
and good to go.

29:42.170 --> 29:44.380
We can go home.

29:44.380 --> 29:46.500
Let's go home.

29:46.500 --> 29:49.830
I'm glad
you're better,

29:49.830 --> 29:52.000
but I'm still
playing catch up, okay.

29:52.000 --> 29:53.580
I just found out
about all this today,

29:53.580 --> 29:55.830
and apparently,
everyone else already knew.

29:59.330 --> 30:00.830
I don't know what
I would do without you.

30:00.830 --> 30:02.000
You know that, right?

30:02.000 --> 30:03.750
Really?
Yeah.

30:03.750 --> 30:06.250
[ Scoffs ]
How was I there for you?

30:06.250 --> 30:07.380
I didn't even know
what was going on.

30:07.380 --> 30:09.210
Gina,
if it wasn't for you,

30:09.210 --> 30:11.210
I would have been dead
a long time ago.

30:14.420 --> 30:17.830
The scary thing is,
I believe that.

30:17.830 --> 30:20.040
I want you to get better.
I want us to be better.

30:20.040 --> 30:21.830
I-I-I know
that you love me,

30:21.830 --> 30:24.000
and I love you, too, baby,
but I...

30:25.830 --> 30:29.580
Right now, I need
to figure out who we are

30:29.580 --> 30:31.120
because I don't know
anymore.

30:38.750 --> 30:39.750
[ Bag unzips ]
Can you tell
I'm nervous?

30:39.750 --> 30:41.080
No.
[ Bag zips ]

30:41.080 --> 30:42.080
It's perfectly normal to change
your shirt 15 times

30:42.080 --> 30:42.920
before going
to play video games.

30:42.920 --> 30:44.670
I really like him.

30:44.670 --> 30:46.170
A lot.

30:46.170 --> 30:48.960
You know what
Dad would say?

30:48.960 --> 30:51.330
"You have to play life
on your terms."

30:51.330 --> 30:53.670
Yeah, well,
he'd be right.

30:53.670 --> 30:56.000
Collar up or down?

30:56.000 --> 30:57.830
Up. It's very
"Risky Business."

30:59.420 --> 31:00.710
Wait in the car.

31:02.210 --> 31:04.460
"Risky Business."
It -- Did I see that?

31:04.460 --> 31:05.710
Why do we bother
with Movie Night

31:05.710 --> 31:07.210
if you're just gonna
fall asleep?

31:07.210 --> 31:10.580
♪♪

31:10.580 --> 31:14.000
Wow. You built the Taj Mahal
in less than a week, honey.

31:14.000 --> 31:15.670
I still have
one spire left,

31:15.670 --> 31:17.460
and Dad didn't help me
one iota.

31:17.460 --> 31:18.750
[ Chuckles ]

31:18.750 --> 31:19.920
How was swimming?

31:19.920 --> 31:21.620
Wet, but fun.

31:21.620 --> 31:23.290
Are you still
in your bathing suit?

31:23.290 --> 31:25.420
Maybe...
Hunter:
Hey, have her call me

31:25.420 --> 31:27.620
as soon as she settles
the LEGO case.

31:27.620 --> 31:28.750
Okay, I have
to go, honey.

31:28.750 --> 31:29.960
I'll call you later
to say good night.

31:29.960 --> 31:31.460
Okay. Bye, Mommy.
I love you.

31:31.460 --> 31:32.880
I love you, too.

31:35.120 --> 31:36.460
What did
Hunter want?

31:36.460 --> 31:39.120
Mm, probably just
to look at you,

31:39.120 --> 31:40.790
but the excuse
was these documents.

31:42.670 --> 31:44.460
You think
he likes me?

31:44.460 --> 31:46.500
No, I know
he likes you.

31:46.500 --> 31:48.960
I'm flattered, but I have
other things to worry about.

31:48.960 --> 31:50.210
No one's
asking you to worry.

31:50.210 --> 31:52.330
It's actually in the fun section
of the program.

31:52.330 --> 31:54.880
Uh, between work and Theo,
I'm too busy for fun.

31:54.880 --> 31:57.670
Great motto, but before you
shell out money for that tattoo,

31:57.670 --> 32:00.750
can I just offer
some unsolicited advice?

32:00.750 --> 32:01.880
When is it
ever solicited?

32:01.880 --> 32:03.250
[ Scoffs ]

32:03.250 --> 32:04.920
The best way
to take care of Theo

32:04.920 --> 32:07.380
is to show him how to live
a full life.

32:07.380 --> 32:08.790
You can't worry so much
about tomorrow

32:08.790 --> 32:10.920
that you forget
to live for today.

32:10.920 --> 32:13.120
Be here.
I am here,

32:13.120 --> 32:14.960
and I'm working.
Oh, boy.

32:14.960 --> 32:18.290
I meant be here,
as in be present

32:18.290 --> 32:20.790
in the large, interconnected
sense of the moment.

32:20.790 --> 32:23.380
Lady, you need to bone up
on your Zen.

32:23.380 --> 32:25.120
I see you
thinking about it.

32:27.250 --> 32:28.880
You sure she's coming?
She's coming.

32:28.880 --> 32:30.790
I don't
want to be late.

32:30.790 --> 32:32.580
Does she like
what you like?

32:32.580 --> 32:34.920
Elliot and I like
all the same things.

32:34.920 --> 32:37.120
Pretty much.

32:37.120 --> 32:39.000
We disagree
over some stuff.

32:39.000 --> 32:41.460
Like what?
Grown-up stuff.

32:41.460 --> 32:43.040
Why don't you worry
about your own date?

32:43.040 --> 32:44.580
I thought it wasn't --
It's not a date.

32:44.580 --> 32:46.420
It's not.

32:46.420 --> 32:48.120
She's here.

32:48.120 --> 32:49.290
Okay, get back
in the car.

32:49.290 --> 32:52.290
Good luck.
Watch and learn, kid.

32:52.290 --> 32:53.330
Good luck.

32:53.330 --> 32:55.170
I hope this is
worth the trip.

32:55.170 --> 32:57.330
Oh, it'll be worth it.
I'll be the judge of that.

32:59.620 --> 33:01.330
[ Goofy voice ]
I've done something crazy.

33:01.330 --> 33:02.580
Oh, what,
parking illegally?

33:02.580 --> 33:04.290
Hi, Danny!

33:04.290 --> 33:05.790
[ Chuckles,
sniffs ]

33:05.790 --> 33:08.000
Ooh, alleyway.

33:08.000 --> 33:09.750
Mmm...nice.

33:09.750 --> 33:10.880
Okay, look up.

33:10.880 --> 33:12.580
Where?

33:15.670 --> 33:17.250
Oh!

33:18.710 --> 33:20.620
That...

33:20.620 --> 33:22.500
is 15 stories,

33:22.500 --> 33:25.290
165 feet, give or take
a recessed ceiling.

33:25.290 --> 33:26.830
It scared
the hell out of me.

33:26.830 --> 33:28.880
It also happens
to be very illegal.

33:28.880 --> 33:32.170
Criminal Code Section 126A --
anyone who intentionally,

33:32.170 --> 33:33.830
willfully,
or wantonly paint--

33:33.830 --> 33:36.750
[ Laughing ]
I love it.

33:36.750 --> 33:40.120
Well, I did it
all for you.
[ Laughs ]

33:40.120 --> 33:42.380
It's pretty amazing,
isn't it?

33:42.380 --> 33:44.170
[ Sighs ]
Oh, wait,
you're the one

33:44.170 --> 33:46.170
who's supposed
to say that.
It's perfect.

33:46.170 --> 33:48.920
It is exactly what
I want the time I
have left to feel like.

33:48.920 --> 33:50.790
"I was here, damn it,
until I wasn't."

33:50.790 --> 33:56.580
♪♪

33:56.580 --> 34:02.670
♪♪

34:02.670 --> 34:03.960
Thank you.

34:06.080 --> 34:07.710
All right,
it's your turn.

34:07.710 --> 34:10.420
[ Sniffles ]
Dare me to do anything,

34:10.420 --> 34:12.040
and make it really hard

34:12.040 --> 34:14.420
because you
outdid yourself.

34:14.420 --> 34:15.830
I dare you
to get chemo.

34:15.830 --> 34:20.750
♪♪

34:20.750 --> 34:22.830
What are you doing,
Gary?
You said
make it really hard.

34:22.830 --> 34:24.960
No, don't.
Don't do that.

34:24.960 --> 34:26.960
That's not fair.
None of this is fair.

34:26.960 --> 34:28.330
That's the whole point,
right?

34:28.330 --> 34:29.920
I mean, you don't
deserve to die.

34:31.670 --> 34:33.620
Game's over.
I'm -- I'm done playing.

34:33.620 --> 34:34.750
[ Sighs ]

34:34.750 --> 34:37.000
Okay, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

34:37.000 --> 34:39.000
I-I take it back.
No, you can't.

34:39.000 --> 34:41.040
We made a deal,
and I was very clear

34:41.040 --> 34:42.290
about what I
needed from you.

34:42.290 --> 34:43.960
Look, I saw the bruise.
Okay, so what?

34:43.960 --> 34:45.750
It's a bruise!

34:45.750 --> 34:48.250
What -- What are you gonna do
when it gets really bad,

34:48.250 --> 34:49.830
when I have sores
all over my body

34:49.830 --> 34:51.380
and I lose
half my weight?

34:51.380 --> 34:54.040
That doesn't have to happen,
and I know it.

34:54.040 --> 34:56.330
So, I'm sorry. Th-Th-That's
the way that I feel.

34:56.330 --> 34:57.500
Well, I don't want you
to feel that!

34:57.500 --> 34:59.580
I don't want you
to feel anything!

34:59.580 --> 35:01.120
Just...

35:01.120 --> 35:02.460
accept what's happening.

35:02.460 --> 35:03.750
That is the whole point.

35:05.540 --> 35:07.920
I'm sorry.
That -- That's up to me.

35:07.920 --> 35:08.960
Okay?

35:10.790 --> 35:12.080
Dr. Stacy was right.

35:14.580 --> 35:16.210
You...

35:16.210 --> 35:17.420
You're so scared.

35:19.540 --> 35:20.750
Of course, I am.

35:23.460 --> 35:25.790
I thought you, of all people,
understood that.

35:29.880 --> 35:31.710
I can't expect you
to do this.

35:31.710 --> 35:35.080
♪♪

35:39.580 --> 35:41.330
You're sure this kid
knows to meet you here?

35:41.330 --> 35:44.290
Yeah.
We texted like 10 times.

35:44.290 --> 35:46.830
He's not coming.

35:46.830 --> 35:49.120
Do you think
he doesn't like me?

35:49.120 --> 35:51.380
I don't know.

35:51.380 --> 35:53.120
Relationships are
complicated, pal.

35:53.120 --> 35:55.500
Men and women,
men and men,

35:55.500 --> 35:57.500
boys and boys, it --

35:57.500 --> 35:59.420
It's not worth
the hassle.

36:00.580 --> 36:02.040
She didn't like
your graffiti, huh?

36:02.040 --> 36:04.750
She did like
the graffiti.

36:04.750 --> 36:07.420
She didn't like
what I said afterwards.

36:07.420 --> 36:09.040
You know what
life's really about?

36:09.040 --> 36:10.670
I'm 12.
Friendship.

36:10.670 --> 36:12.290
You and me.

36:12.290 --> 36:13.790
Right here, dude.

36:13.790 --> 36:15.460
Yeah. Us.

36:15.460 --> 36:16.830
That's what it's about.

36:19.580 --> 36:21.290
Oh.

36:21.290 --> 36:24.080
What's up?

36:24.080 --> 36:26.120
Ahh!

36:26.120 --> 36:27.210
[ Exhales deeply ]

36:27.210 --> 36:28.460
Hi.
Hey.

36:28.460 --> 36:29.960
I'm Elliot.
I know who you are, kid.

36:29.960 --> 36:32.120
It's good to meet you.
It's good to meet you, too.

36:32.120 --> 36:34.000
Okay, let's go.

36:34.000 --> 36:35.920
Okay.

36:35.920 --> 36:40.960
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

36:40.960 --> 36:44.750
♪♪

36:44.750 --> 36:48.710
♪ You could never know
what it's like ♪

36:48.710 --> 36:53.420
♪ Your blood, like winter,
freezes just like ice ♪

36:53.420 --> 36:55.420
[ Chuckles softly ]

36:55.420 --> 36:57.580
You want to go on a date
with me sometime?

36:57.580 --> 36:58.670
A date?

37:01.080 --> 37:02.960
Yeah.

37:02.960 --> 37:04.620
Maybe.

37:04.620 --> 37:06.210
You should
probably know...

37:08.210 --> 37:10.540
...I'm married.

37:10.540 --> 37:12.000
Really?

37:14.210 --> 37:16.080
Well, I am, too.

37:17.540 --> 37:20.380
My name's Rome,
by the way.

37:20.380 --> 37:22.250
Regina.

37:22.250 --> 37:23.580
Nice to meet you.

37:25.380 --> 37:26.580
[ Whispering ] It's nice
to meet you, too.

37:26.580 --> 37:28.670
♪ I'm still standing ♪

37:28.670 --> 37:32.540
♪ Better than I ever did ♪

37:32.540 --> 37:36.080
♪ Looking like a true survivor ♪

37:36.080 --> 37:37.380
♪ Feeling like a little kid ♪
Hey, Uncle Gary.

37:37.380 --> 37:39.210
You want
to play with us?

37:39.210 --> 37:41.670
Oh...
This place is awesome.

37:41.670 --> 37:43.620
It's awesome.

37:43.620 --> 37:44.880
Okay, well,

37:44.880 --> 37:48.170
prepare to be crushed
in "Frogger."

37:48.170 --> 37:50.250
No, no, no,
we'll see about that.
Will we, then? Okay.

37:50.250 --> 37:52.170
